<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-062-108 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 253 601</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Sept 9 1991 n437 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Lotus scuttles Galileo. (Lotus Development Corp.'s softwaredistribution program called Lotus Choices)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Darrow, Barbara.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Lotus Development Corp quietly discontinues its innovative Galileoor Lotus Choices program of bundling software programs withcertain microcomputers for promotional purposes.andP;  The discontinuedprogram called for Lotus to include copies of Lotus 1-2-3,Freelance Plus and Magellan on the hard disk of microcomputersmade by Compaq, IBM, Panasonic and Toshiba.andP;  It also called forjoint management by ComputerLand Canada.andP;  The software could besampled and used by consumers up to seven times before it wasdisabled.andP;  Consumers could then use their credit cards to purchaseany of the packages they desired.andP;  Lotus representatives citeddisappointing sales results as the main factor in thecancellation.andP;  Another factor in Lotus' decision may have beenpressure from other retailers who feared that such a program mightdisrupt the reseller channel.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Lotus Development Corp. (Marketing).andO;Ticker:    LOTS.andO;Topic:     Promotion of ProductMarketing StrategyPilot ProjectsBundled SoftwareVendor RelationsDistribution Management.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>